body:
# Run Assistant on Thread

Runs execute an assistant against a thread, processing messages, invoking tools, and generating responses.

## Create and Poll

The simplest approach — create a run and automatically poll until completion:

```javascript
import OpenAI from "openai";

const client = new OpenAI();

const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.createAndPoll(threadId, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
});

if (run.status === "completed") {
  const messages = await client.beta.threads.messages.list(threadId, {
    order: "desc",
    limit: 1,
  });
  console.log(messages.data[0].content[0].text.value);
} else {
  console.error(`Run failed with status: ${run.status}`);
}
```

## Manual Polling

For more control over the polling interval and status handling:

```javascript
// Create the run
let run = await client.beta.threads.runs.create(threadId, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
});

// Poll until terminal status
while (["queued", "in_progress", "cancelling"].includes(run.status)) {
  await new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, 1000));
  run = await client.beta.threads.runs.retrieve(threadId, run.id);
  console.log(`Status: ${run.status}`);
}

switch (run.status) {
  case "completed":
    console.log("Run completed successfully.");
    break;
  case "requires_action":
    console.log("Run needs tool call results.");
    break;
  case "failed":
    console.error(`Failed: ${run.last_error?.message}`);
    break;
  case "expired":
    console.error("Run expired (tool outputs not submitted within 10 minutes).");
    break;
}
```

## Streaming Runs

Stream run events for real-time output:

```javascript
const stream = client.beta.threads.runs.stream(threadId, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
});

for await (const event of stream) {
  if (event.event === "thread.message.delta") {
    const content = event.data.delta.content?.[0]?.text?.value || "";
    process.stdout.write(content);
  }
  if (event.event === "thread.run.requires_action") {
    // Handle tool calls — see below
  }
}
```

## Handling Tool Calls (requires_action)

When the assistant invokes functions, the run pauses with `requires_action` status:

```javascript
if (run.status === "requires_action") {
  const toolCalls = run.required_action.submit_tool_outputs.tool_calls;

  const toolOutputs = await Promise.all(
    toolCalls.map(async (toolCall) => {
      const args = JSON.parse(toolCall.function.arguments);
      let output;

      switch (toolCall.function.name) {
        case "get_weather":
          output = await getWeather(args.location);
          break;
        case "search_database":
          output = await searchDB(args.query);
          break;
        default:
          output = { error: `Unknown function: ${toolCall.function.name}` };
      }

      return {
        tool_call_id: toolCall.id,
        output: JSON.stringify(output),
      };
    })
  );

  // Submit outputs and continue the run
  run = await client.beta.threads.runs.submitToolOutputsAndPoll(threadId, run.id, {
    tool_outputs: toolOutputs,
  });
}
```

## Run with Overrides

Override assistant settings per-run:

```javascript
const run = await client.beta.threads.runs.create(threadId, {
  assistant_id: "asst_abc123",
  additional_instructions: "Respond in Spanish for this request.",
  max_prompt_tokens: 4000,
  max_completion_tokens: 1000,
  truncation_strategy: {
    type: "last_messages",
    last_messages: 5,
  },
  temperature: 0.3,
});
```

## Run Status Lifecycle

```
queued -> in_progress -> completed
                      -> requires_action -> (submit tool outputs) -> in_progress -> completed
                      -> failed
                      -> cancelling -> cancelled
                      -> expired
```

| Status | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `queued` | Run is waiting to start |
| `in_progress` | Assistant is generating a response |
| `requires_action` | Waiting for tool call results |
| `completed` | Run finished successfully |
| `failed` | Run encountered an error |
| `cancelling` | Cancellation requested |
| `cancelled` | Run was cancelled |
| `expired` | Tool outputs not submitted within 10 minutes |

